snippet.textDisplay: This is a blissful song, an extraterrestrial blend of instruments and beautiful vocals. I don't know where do you guys manage to get such wonderful singers man. You guys have a Midas Touch in Music, not gonna lie. From, Muaziz Saarif, Thagyan, Ye Dunya, Phir Milenge, Pasoori to this, OMG, You are on fire. As an Indian, I can definitely vouch for the fact that.Coke Studio Pakistan has undoubtedly better releases than their counterpart here in India, and I love listening to you guys. Keep up the good work man. I have a bad voice or I would say, a mere Bathroom singer here, but my heart longs to visit Pakistan and sing in one of your songs there, while I listen to these masterpieces. Let me know if you have a spot for singer😌 Nevertheless, Keep em coming🔥

That is truly beautiful. I deeply wish to visit my native Sindh. The Sindhi people and their culture are so often misunderstood and underrated. Their hard work and resilience have been overlooked, simply because they don't seek to preach or showcase themselves. I hope this song sparks a narrative that unveils all their untold stories.❤❤❤

You might find it surprising that many Bollywood stars are Sindhi, or have Sindhi mothers, yet they often hide this and identify as Punjabi instead. It's truly saddening.

Pl keep up the good work 

You really stirred my emotions, I feel so touched by this song I can really feel all the emotions you want to convey.
Love from 🇮🇳
